ZH: 礼貌是社会的基本规范。
EN: Politeness is a basic norm of society.

ZH: 学会尊重他人就是一种礼。
EN: Learning to respect others is a form of courtesy.

ZH: 父母教会我们要有礼貌。
EN: Our parents teach us to be polite.

ZH: 礼多人不怪。
EN: It is never too much to be courteous.

ZH: 礼义廉耻是中华民族的传统美德。
EN: Ritual, righteousness, integrity, and shame are traditional virtues of the Chinese nation.

ZH: 礼让他人就是尊重别人。
EN: Yielding to others is a way of showing respect to them.

ZH: 礼尚往来。
EN: Courtesy demands reciprocity.

ZH: 他的一举一动都充满了礼。
EN: His every move is filled with courtesy.

ZH: 金无足赤人无完人，不求善人谓礼。
EN: Gold can never be pure, and people can never be complete, but never call a good person lacking in courtesy.

ZH: 用礼待人，才能得到他人的尊重。
EN: Treat others with courtesy, and you will earn their respect.

ZH: 礼乐文化是中华民族的瑰宝。
EN: The culture of ceremony and music is a treasure of the Chinese nation.

ZH: 礼敬先贤是我们的传统。
EN: Paying tribute to the ancestors is our tradition.

ZH: 如果你不能给别人幸福，就给别人礼。
EN: If you cannot give happiness to others, give them courtesy.

ZH: 礼尚往来，言而有信。
EN: Courtesy demands reciprocity, and promises must be kept.

ZH: 礼貌常常比实际行动更重要。
EN: Politeness is often more important than actual actions.

ZH: 礼仪起源于古代社会。
EN: Etiquette originated in ancient society.

ZH: 礼节是人际交往的基本规则。
EN: Etiquette is the foundation of interpersonal communication.

ZH: 他是个礼貌的绅士。
EN: He is a polite gentleman.

ZH: 世界各地的礼俗各不相同。
EN: Customs and manners vary in different parts of the world.

ZH: 礼貌是一种美德。
EN: Politeness is a virtue.
